This topic describes how to install and configure VictoriaMetrics for VMware Tanzu.

##<a id='install'></a> Install and Configure VictoriaMetrics for VMware Tanzu

1. Download the product file from Pivotal Network.

1. Navigate to the **Ops Manager Installation Dashboard** and click **Import a Product** to upload the product file.

1. Under the **Import a Product** button, click **+** next to the version number of VictoriaMetrics for VMware Tanzu.
This adds the tile to your staging area.

1. Click the newly added **VictoriaMetrics for VMware Tanzu** tile.

1. Set up the network for the tile:
  <%= image_tag("images/networks.png") %>

1. Click **Save**.

1. Configure settings (enabled by default):
  <%= image_tag("images/settings.png") %>

1. Click **Save**.

1. Return to the **Ops Manager Installation Dashboard**

1. Click **Review Pending Changes** and click **Apply changes** to install **VictoriaMetrics for VMware Tanzu** tile.
